# Code-factory HIGH-risk path ownership — VARIANT: astro / static / no-Convex
# (e.g. astro-starter, speech-sprout, cheeky-panda, royal-essence — Astro/HTML/Shopify
# sites with no convex/ backend; the "backend" is serverless API routes + config).
# Drop at .github/CODEOWNERS. Only HIGH-risk paths get an owner; low/medium paths are
# intentionally UNOWNED so green checks alone permit merge. One high-risk file elevates the
# whole PR. The HARD gate is .github/workflows/high-risk-guard.yml (required status check);
# this file is defense-in-depth + documentation. See skills/kb-code-factory.
#
# @pauljohnchamberlain (org admin) bypasses via the ruleset + high-risk-guard's author===OWNER
# logic, so HIS PRs never block here; this gate exists for kaizen-brands-agents[bot] PRs.

# Backend equivalent — serverless / API routes + server config (no Convex here)
**/pages/api/                  @pauljohnchamberlain
**/server/                     @pauljohnchamberlain
**/*.config.*                  @pauljohnchamberlain

# Auth (if present)
**/auth/                       @pauljohnchamberlain
**/auth.ts                     @pauljohnchamberlain
**/better-auth*                @pauljohnchamberlain

# Payments / billing (if present)
**/stripe*                     @pauljohnchamberlain
**/payment*                    @pauljohnchamberlain
**/billing*                    @pauljohnchamberlain

# Infra / CI / secrets / deploy config
/.github/                      @pauljohnchamberlain
*.tf                           @pauljohnchamberlain
**/vercel.json                 @pauljohnchamberlain
**/wrangler.*                  @pauljohnchamberlain
**/middleware.*                @pauljohnchamberlain
**/.env*                       @pauljohnchamberlain

# Dependency manifests (supply chain) — Dependabot's own PRs flow via dependabot-automerge.yml
